@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>


<div class="privacy-policy-small">
    <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>
        <strong>CineLog</strong> is a non-commercial, personal movie logging and discovery application. Your privacy and data security are important to us. This policy explains how we handle your information during testing and use of CineLog.
    </p>

    <h3>What Data We Collect</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Email address and display name (if you register or use Google login).</li>
        <li><strong>Movie Data:</strong> Movies you log, wishlists, blacklists, ratings, and related preferences.</li>
        <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Basic analytics (e.g., page visits, feature usage) for improving CineLog.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>How We Use Your Data</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Your data is used only to provide CineLog features (movie logging, suggestions, wishlists, etc.).</li>
        <li>We do not sell, share, or use your data for advertising or commercial purposes.</li>
        <li>All data is stored securely in Azure cloud infrastructure.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Third-Party Services</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>TMDB:</strong> CineLog uses The Movie Database (TMDB) API for movie data. TMDB does not receive your personal information.</li>
        <li><strong>Google Login:</strong> If you use Google authentication, your email and display name are used for login only.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Data Retention & Deletion</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Test data may be deleted before public launch. Contact the project owner to request data removal at any time.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Non-Commercial Use</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>CineLog is for personal and testing use only. No fees, subscriptions, or commercial activities are involved.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Contact</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>For questions or data removal requests, contact the project owner at the email provided during testing.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>TMDB Disclaimer</h3>
    <p>
        This product uses the TMDB API but is not endorsed or certified by TMDB.
    </p>
</div>

